    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SWISSAIR EYES BRAZIL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's four major airlines, Vasp, Varig, Transbrazil and TAM, are in talks with Swissair about possible partnerships (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The four main airlines in Brazil are in discussions with Swissair, part of SAirGroup, about possible partnerships. Swissair said it wanted to add flights to Brazil after the cancellation of such flights by the most financially troubled of the four carriers, Vasp. Under Brazilian law, foreigners can own up to 20 percent of a domestic airline. Vasp, Varig, Transbrazil and TAM are all struggling with heavy debts and the effects of a currency devaluation last year.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
